Job Responsibilities:-


Prepare companies for fund raising and/or IPO by analyzing their financial information, preparing financial projections and assisting them in preparing financial and management accounts;
Conduct financial due diligence potential acquisition targets by collecting detailed information and conducting interviews; collate, analyze the information and prepare a detailed due diligence report;
Be the acting CFO of a client; prepare and review monthly/quarterly consolidated financial information; manage cash position, cashflow projection; analyze and compare company forecasts and budgets;
Work with a team of professionals, auditors, financial advisors, valuers and lawyers to perform consulting/advisory projects; and
Assist in compliance including company secretarial matters for private companies in Hong Kong; cross-border company setup and transactions in Hong Kong & China.
 

Job Requirements: -

Bachelor degree or above in Accounting or Finance, (HKICPA, CIA or ACCA preferred);
At least 2-years relevant working experience;
Good grasp of Microsoft Office applications such as excel and powerpoint;
Good communication and presentation skills and sense of servicing awareness;
Good command in English and Mandarin (listening, oral, reading and writing) is a must; good communication and presentation skills in English and Mandarin.
Experience in using Xero, CRM applications (such as ZOHO) is a plus.
Applicants with international background preferred;
Entrepreneurial mindset, intellectual curiosity, structured thinking, innovative, and embraces change and disruption;
Honest, reliable, responsible, focus on teamwork, open minded, willing to learn;

Responsibilities:   

Produce the monthly and quarterly Group financial reporting, management reporting and financial analysis;
Perform daily accounting function;
Participate in annual budget preparation, financial analysis and forecasting;
Liaise with external auditors, professional parties;
Assist Finance Manager/Financial Controller to perform ad hoc projects

 Requirements:

Degree in Accountancy or related disciplines;
3-5 years auditing/accounting experiences;
Familiar with computerized accounting system and software, eg. ERP or POS;
Superior knowledge of MS Excel;
Detail-minded, proactive, independent, under pressure and meet tight deadline;
Good command of both spoken and written in Cantonese, English and Mandarin;
Immediate availability is highly preferred

We are equal opportunity employer with good work environment. We offer attractive salary, training opportunity, and staff purchase discount. Please send your application with resume and expected salary to HR Department, Office Tower 8/F, 807-811, Hutchison Logistics Centre, 18 Container Port Road South, Kwai Chung or send your application by clicking “Apply Now”.


All applications will be treated in strict confidence and all personal data collected will be used for recruitment purposes only.

Our client is a Listed group,  Current they are looking for potential candidate to join their Finance team in Hong Kong.

Responsibilities;

Report to Head of Finance (General Account & Finance Analysis);
To Lead a small team of Finance Operation Team in Hong Kong;

Handle full set of account including operaton /finance analysis/ management account etc;
To perform and lead the accounting process and procedure, ensuring compliance with the accounting policies and guidelines;
Lead and coaching to a small team to manage accounting reporting & reporting;
Good communcation with English and Chinese is must.
Requirements:

Degree or Above in Accounting or related discipline;

Holder of CPA professional qualification and experience in 4A CPA Firm is a plus;
About 8+  years working experience in Full set of accounting and Management Accounting;
Experience in Multi-national group is preferred;
Solid Experience in Asia Pacific Trading Business is preferred;
Good experience in dealing with various country business user;
Using software with MS Office (Execl, Word, Powerpoint) and Oracle Finance is a plus;
Excellent spoken and written communication skill in English;
Work independently and good team leadership.
Our client will offer competitive remuneration package and good career prospects to the potential candidate, interested parties please quote ref.no.FM-0117-sh-JDB and submit your resume to Ms Fung by our email or enquiry with Tel:3428-6121.


All profiles are handled with strictest confidentiality. Shortlisted candidates would be notified
